# SkyWeb Change Log

Detailed implementation history for SkyWeb Analytics. README stays focused on current state and run instructions.

## DN-4 — Public Macro REST Endpoints in C#

- Added native ASP.NET Core/C# public macro endpoint family under `/api/public/macro/*`.
- Added `PublicMacroController`, `PublicMacroService`, and `MacroReadService`.
- Ported public macro view/indicator registry and SQL read behavior from SkyServer Node services.
- Preserved public API response contracts: `{ ok: true, ... }`, public view payloads, indicator payloads, pagination fields, and service-style error responses.
- Removed `/api/public/macro/*` from the temporary SkyServer proxy bridge so public macro reads are served by `SkyWeb.Api`.
- Left `/api/auth/*` and `/api/skyweb/*` proxied to SkyServer for the next migration stages.
- Confirmed `.NET` lane client port convention: existing SkyWeb app on `5174`, copied .NET-lane client on `5175`.

## DN-3 — .NET Client Wiring + Proxy Bridge

- Wired copied `SkyWeb.Client` to call `SkyWeb.Api` first.
- Added temporary proxy fallback from `SkyWeb.Api` to SkyServer Node API for unported route families.
- Added support for `VITE_SKYWEB_API_BASE_URL`.
- Established side-by-side local development flow: SkyServer Node API, SkyWeb.Api, and SkyWeb.Client.

## DN-0 to DN-2 — .NET Transition Foundation

- Preserved pre-.NET baseline.
- Added `apps/web-dotnet` with `SkyWeb.DotNet.sln`, `SkyWeb.Api`, and copied `SkyWeb.Client`.
- Added health and DB health endpoints: `/_health` and `/_db/health`.
- Added Swagger, CORS, Dapper, Npgsql, and camelCase JSON serialization.

## Phase 8 — Macro Alerts

- Added alert rules, evaluation history, scheduled evaluation visibility, triggered notification queue, app-wide signal surfacing, alert preferences, dedicated Signal Center, and alert-rule UX polish.

## Phase 7 — Saved Dashboards and Watchlists

- Added personalized dashboard builder, dashboard viewer, presentation route, reusable dashboard items, and saved/pinned macro view workflows.

## Phase 1 to Phase 6 — Foundation through Preferences

- Built SkyWeb React/Vite shell, public macro API consumption, macro overview/detail surfaces, auth shell, member account route, profile/preferences UI, and dashboard/chart polish.
